                <p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/the-alters/" data-ref-id="5000-566112">The Alters</a> developer 11 Bit Studios has found itself in hot water after players discovered evidence of generative AI in the game. The studio has now released a statement to explain why AI chatbot prompts can be found in multiple parts of the introspective survival game.</p><p>After The Alters was released in mid-June, screenshots started to emerge on social media showing evidence that certain content had been generated by AI chatbots--despite the game lacking the AI disclosure that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/game-developers-will-need-to-disclose-ai-use-on-steam/1100-6520235/" data-ref-id="1100-6520235">Steam now requires from developers</a>.</p>



    
